# Pem — Core engineering (AI + real-time)

## Vercel AI SDK — never use generateObject / streamObject

Use **`generateText`** with **`Output.object({ schema })`** and Zod. See AI SDK 6 migration.

```typescript
import { generateText, Output } from 'ai'

const result = await generateText({
  model: openai('gpt-4o-mini'),
  output: Output.object({ schema: mySchema }),
  prompt: '...',
})
// result.output — typed from schema
```

## SSE (inbox extraction)

After **`POST /dumps`**, the client connects to **`GET /inbox/stream?dumpId=`** with auth. Server publishes over Redis: **`item.created`**, **`inbox.updated`**, **`stream.done`**. Same Nest **`@Sse`** + Redis pub/sub pattern as before; events are inbox-scoped, not prep-scoped.

## Push

Payload **`kind: inbox_updated`** — client may deep link to **`/inbox`**.
